S . AFRICA ANNOUNCES SUPPLY SIDE INVESTMENT MEASURES . South Africa ' s Department of Trade and Industry said on Wednesday it was launching two supply - side industrial incentive programmes designed to encourage investment . Under the Tax Holiday Scheme , new investments in manufacturing with assets exceeding three million rand will be zero taxed for six years , if they meet qualifying criteria including human resources , location and industry sector . The Small / Medium Manufacturing Development Scheme , which replaces the existing Simplified Regional Industrial Development Programme , will allow firms investing three million rand to qualify for start - up grants . - - Johannesburg newsroom + 27 11 482 1003 
